### Unicode

The main article for this thrilling topic is [Samaritan (Unicode block)](/Samaritan_(Unicode_block)).

The Samaritan script was finally added to the [Unicode](/Unicode) Standard in October 2009 with the release of version 5.2. This means your computer can now properly render the characters of an ancient liturgical language, a task I'm sure it performs with as much enthusiasm as I'm mustering right now.

The Unicode block for Samaritan is U+0800–U+083F. Here it is, in all its codified glory.

